gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 124, Nets 120
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Stephen Curry’s 37 points (16 in the 4th quarter) and six 3PM, the Warriors defeated the Nets, 124-120. Klay Thompson (24 points, four 3PM) and Brandin Podziemski (19 points, four 3PM) added a combined 43 points for the Warriors in the victory, while Cam Thomas tallied 41 points for the Nets in the losing effort. The Warriors improve to 11-14 on the season, while the Nets fall to 13-12.
